      "Python is a high‑level, interpreted programming language known for its readability, simplicity, and versatility. It was created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991. Python emphasizes clear, concise syntax (often called “executable pseudocode”) and supports multiple programming paradigms, including procedural, object‑oriented, and functional styles.\n",
      "\n",
      "Key features:\n",
      "\n",
      "- **Easy to learn and use** – its syntax is designed to be intuitive, making it popular for beginners and experienced developers alike.\n",
      "- **Dynamic typing** – variables don’t need explicit type declarations.\n",
      "- **Extensive standard library** – “batteries‑included” modules for file I/O, networking, web services, data manipulation, and more.\n",
      "- **Cross‑platform** – runs on Windows, macOS, Linux, and many other operating systems.\n",
      "- **Large ecosystem** – thousands of third‑party packages available via PyPI (Python Package Index) for web development, scientific computing, machine learning, automation, and more.\n",
